-- Swansea Beats Fulham 3-0 for Third Straight Premier League Win
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-03-17T17:06:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-17/swansea-beats-fulham-3-0-for-third-straight-premier-league-win.html
Gylfi Sigurdsson scored two goals
as Swansea beat Fulham 3-0 for its third straight win in English
soccer’s Premier League.  Joe Allen  also scored at Craven Cottage in  London  as the
Swans moved up three places in the standings to eighth place
with 39 points. Fulham lost its second straight to drop one spot
to 11th place.  Paul Scharner’s goal in the 65th minute gave West Bromwich
a 1-1 tie at Wigan. James McArthur scored in the 54th minute for
Wigan, which is winless in 13 home matches and remains in last
place with 22 points.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  